== Walnut Gremolata and Stewed White Beans ==

Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Roughly chop @walnuts{1/2%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine scallion greens, walnuts, @olive oil{2%tsp}, juice from one lemon wedge, a pinch of lemon zest, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant and tender, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in beans, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, ¼ cup water, a pinch of salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook, mashing about half the beans with the back of a #wooden spoon{}, until beans are creamy and thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @crème fraîche{2%tbsp}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Keep covered until ready to serve.

== Herbed Chicken ==

While beans cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

> Swap in pork chops for chicken if preferred.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep warm. Let pan cool for ~{1%minute}, then wipe out pan.

== Sauce and Assembly ==

Heat same pan over medium heat. Add @red pepper jam{1}, ¼ cup water, and @butter{1%tbsp}; cook, whisking, until butter has melted and sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Slice chicken crosswise.

> Slice pork crosswise if using pork chops.

Divide beans between shallow #bowls{} and top with sliced chicken. Spoon pan sauce over chicken and top with gremolata. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.